## One law

> **~10 min = Auto Runtime trigger = one Cloud Forge Run POST = 100 rows DOWN (mandatory). NOT “up to 100.” NOT drain/loop in founder chat. See `038-cloud-forge-run-vocabulary-v1.mdc`.**

## Primary API (founder cockpit)

```bash
POST http://127.0.0.1:13027/api/cloud-workers/v1
{"action":"proceed","full_pack":true,"max_advance":100,"llm_provider":"openrouter"}
```

## Agents MUST

- Point founder to **Cloud Workers.app** Proceed — not Worker Hub :13020
- Read [queue](https://sourcea-fbe-runner-production.up.railway.app/api/cloud-forge-run/queue/v1) for `cloud_forge_run_head` · `batch_id` · `queue_batch_complete`
- Proof of drain = head advances through batch range (e.g. 201→300), not observer alone
- After Railway deploy, verify queue head/batch — `/health` PASS alone is not proof
- If deploy built but queue still shows old batch, run queue action `sync_pointer_from_image` once, then re-read queue

## Agents MUST NOT

- Change drain to single-cycle-per-cron (INCIDENT-042)
- Say "open Worker Hub.app first" for Cloud Forge Run
- Run `portfolio_competitor_forge_dispatch_v1.py --full-motor` on Mac for CLOUD-SEC rows
- Deploy Railway without Dockerfile COPY for active batch JSON
- Redeploy repeatedly when the only blocker is stale Railway volume pointer; use `sync_pointer_from_image`

